# Form field spacing

Stacked labels and controls should follow **`src/components/ui/field.tsx`** primitives so spacing matches the design system and administration forms.

## Side sheets and modals

The same **`Field` / `FieldGroup` / `FieldLabel`** rules apply inside **`SheetContent`** and similar narrow editors — not only full-width pages. Do not drop down to raw **`Label` + `space-y-*`** in sheets “to save space”; use the primitives. See **`.cursor/rules/admin-editor-sheet-no-form-container.mdc`** for the full sheet checklist.

## Within one field (label → control)

- Use **`Field`** with **`FieldLabel`** and the control as siblings.
- Vertical spacing is **`gap-4`** (16px / 1rem) — do not replace with ad‑hoc `space-y-2` / `mt-3` on the control.

## Between separate fields (group to group)

- Wrap stacked fields in **`FieldGroup`**.
- Spacing between fields is **`gap-8`** (32px / 2rem). This is ~2× the label-to-control gap so groups read as distinct.

## Dense layouts

- Multi-column **grids** of short fields may use **`gap-6`** (24px) between cells when **`gap-8`** feels too loose (e.g. settings cards with many small inputs).

## Checkbox / radio (control beside text)

- Keep **`Checkbox` / `RadioGroupItem` + `Label`** in a row with **`gap-3`** (12px) between control and text unless a specific pattern already defines spacing.

## React Hook Form (`FormItem`)

- **`FormItem`** in `src/components/ui/form.tsx` uses **`space-y-4`** between label, control, description, and message — align new RHF forms with that stack.

## Do not

- Mix **`Label` + `className="mt-3"`** on inputs for vertical stacks; use **`Field` / `FieldLabel`** instead.
- Rely on **`Label` + `space-y-2`** or outer **`space-y-4`** alone for vertical stacks of inputs — use **`FieldGroup` + `Field`** (especially in **sheets**).
